In the Matter of the Claim of Fannie Farber, Appellant, v. U. S. Trucking Corp., Respondent. Workmen’s Compensation Board, Respondent. Submitted July 9, 1964; decided July 10, 1964. Jeannette H. Harris, Louis Raybin and Jacques Smit for motion.

No one opposed.

Motion granted and appeal dismissed, without costs and without prejudice, upon the ground that the order appealed from does not finally determine the proceeding within the meaning of the Constitution.
